data.enText: the amount of space that an object or a substance fills; the amount of space that a container has

data.chText: 你如何计量气体的体积？
data.enText: How do you measure the volume of a gas?
the sheer volume (= large amount) of business

data.chText: 这项工作的量最近增加了。
data.enText: This work has grown in volume recently.

data.chText: 正在修建新的道路以应付增加了的交通量。
data.enText: New roads are being built to cope with the increased volume of traffic.

data.chText: 六月份的销售额下降了0.2%。

data.enText: the amount of sound that is produced by a television, radio, etc.
a book, that is part of a series of books

data.chText: 卷，合订本（同一杂志的一系列期刊，尤指一年的）
data.enText: a series of different issues of the same magazine, especially all the issues for one year

simple_means.memory_skill: vol 卷，转 + ume → 装订成卷 → 卷，册

ex.enText: What size shoe do you wear?

ex.chText: 这套公寓的面积大约有300平方英尺。
ex.enText: This apartment is roughly 300 square feet in size.

ex.chText: 我们把小组的人数从15人减少到5人。
ex.enText: We decreased the size of the group from 15 to 5.

synonyms.bx: 主要指尺码、规模、面积、身材等的大小，也指数量、数额等的多少。

ex.chText: 体积大并不总是意味着分量重。
ex.enText: Great bulk does not always mean great weight.

ex.chText: 这是一份篇幅惊人的文件。
ex.enText: It was a document of surprising bulk.

synonyms.bx: 不用于准确的度量，只表示相当大的体积或数量。

ex.enText: What are the dimensions of this room?

ex.chText: 宽度也是一种线性尺寸。
ex.enText: Width is a linear dimension, too.

ex.chText: 我的父母买了一所宽敞的房屋。
ex.enText: My parents have bought a house of generous dimensions.

synonyms.bx: 指物体的面积、容积、规模等，通常用复数。

ex.chText: 空气变热时，其体积便迅速膨胀。
ex.enText: When the air becomes hot, its volume increases rapidly.

ex.chText: 这个箱子的容积为180立方英尺。
ex.enText: The volume of this box is 180 cubic feet.

ex.chText: 与巴西的贸易额增加了。
ex.enText: The volume of business with Brazil has increased.

synonyms.bx: 指某物的体积或某容器的容积或容量，也可指生产、贸易、销售等的数量或数额。

data.enText: to tell you a lot about sth/sb, without the need for words

tr: physical objects consisting of a number of pages bound together
example: he used a large book as a doorstop

tr: the magnitude of sound (usually in a specified direction)
example: the kids played their music at full volume

tr: the property of something that is great in magnitude
example: it is cheaper to buy it in bulk
he received a mass of correspondence

tr: a publication that is one of a set of several similar publications
example: he asked for the 1989 volume of the Annual Review

tr: the amount of 3-dimensional space occupied by an object
example: the gas expanded to twice its original volume
mix one volume of the solution with ten volumes of water

value.def: The volume of something is the amount of it that there is.

example.ex: Senior officials will be discussing how the volume of sales might be reduced.
example.tran: 高层领导将要讨论销售量如何削减。

example.ex: ...the sheer volume of traffic and accidents.
example.tran: 交通流量之大、事故之多

value.def: The volume of an object is the amount of space that it contains or occupies.

example.ex: It is 2,300 metres above sea level, so a given volume of air contains only about one-third as much oxygen as it would at sea level...
example.tran: 这是在海拔2,300米的高空，因此一定体积空气的含氧量只有海平面处的约1/3。

example.ex: When egg whites are beaten they can rise to seven or eight times their original volume.
example.tran: 蛋清打散后，体积可增至原来的七八倍。

value.def: A volume is one book in a series of books.
A volume is a collection of several issues of a magazine, for example all the issues for one year.
The volume of a radio, television, or sound system is the loudness of the sound it produces.

example.ex: He came to complain about the volume of the music.
example.tran: 他过来抱怨音乐的音量太高了。

value.tran: （广播、电视或音响系统的）音量，声量,响度

value.def: If something such as an action speaks volumes about a person or thing, it gives you a lot of information about them.

example.ex: What you wear speaks volumes about you...
example.tran: 你的衣着能传递很多关于你的信息。
他们的缺席已经充分说明了问题。

value.tran: 清楚表明;详尽说明;充分说明
